form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony, N-4-55

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/25/2023 ELM U.S. Department of Justice OMB No. 1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony AR#: 43 136 069 Date: Thursday, October 21 1999 GREGORIANA ALVAREZ-GONZALEZ <1645 so CATALINA ST #202 LOS ANGELES CA 90006 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony on: Thursday, October 28 1999 at: LOS ANGELES CONVENTION CENTER RAFACS 1201 SOUTH FIGUEROA STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 DEC 10 1999 ROOM NUMBER: HALL Please report promptly at 1:00 PM. UMEL-DENY F/HEAR 12/2/99 8:39 You must bring the following with you: This letter, WITH ALL OF THE QUESTIONS ON THE OTHER SIDE ANSWERED IN INK OR ON A TYPEWRITER. Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit, or Refugee Travel Document. Any Immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is on behalf of your child(children), bring your child (children). Other PLEASE BRING A WHEELCHAIR IF YOU CANNOT STAND FOR LONG OR WALK LONG DISTANCES If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, you will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445 (Rev. 1/8/92) (SEE OTHER SIDE)
